# Project Structure Rules

This document defines the structure rules for the folder-web project.

## Directory Structure

- [folder-web/index.html](mdc:folder-web/index.html) - Main HTML file
- [folder-web/style.css](mdc:folder-web/style.css) - Global CSS styles
- [folder-web/scripts/](mdc:folder-web/scripts) - JavaScript files
- [folder-web/static/](mdc:folder-web/static) - Static assets (images, fonts, etc.)

## HTML Structure Guidelines

- HTML files should use semantic HTML5 elements (header, nav, main, section, article, footer)
- All HTML files must be properly indented and formatted
- No inline styles or JavaScript should be used within HTML files
- Use meaningful class names following a consistent naming convention

## CSS Guidelines

- All styles must be defined in [folder-web/style.css](mdc:folder-web/style.css)
- CSS should follow a mobile-first responsive design approach
- Use media queries for responsive design
- Avoid using !important unless absolutely necessary
- Use CSS variables for colors, fonts, and other repeated values

## JavaScript Guidelines

- All JavaScript files must be placed in the [folder-web/scripts/](mdc:folder-web/scripts) directory
- JavaScript should be loaded at the end of the HTML body
- Use modern ES6+ JavaScript features when appropriate
- Avoid using global variables
- All JavaScript should be properly commented
